name: CDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxyglucose reductase
classes: Acting on CH or CH2 groups;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose + NAD(P)+ + H2O = CDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-glucose + NAD(P)H + H+ [RN:R03391 R03392]
comment: The enzyme consists of two proteins. One forms an enzyme-bound adduct of the CDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxyglucose with pyridoxamine phosphate, in which the 3-hydroxy group has been removed. The second catalyses the reduction of this adduct by NAD(P)H and release of the CDP-4-dehydro-3,6-dideoxy-D-glucose and pyridoxamine phosphate.

pathways.ec00520: Amino sugar and nucleotide sugar metabolism
